# dotnet-semantic-search â€” Cursor rules (repository)

These rules apply to all edits in this repo. Prefer matching existing patterns: modern C# (nullable reference types, implicit usings where projects already enable them), **.NET 9**, **Microsoft.Extensions.AI**, and the layout under **`code/`**.

## Solution layout and shared code

- **Solution root:** `code/dotnet-semantic-search.sln`.
- **`code/dotnet-semantic-search/`** â€” console app for RSS ingest, embeddings, and Cosmos writes; also the **shared class library** referenced by the API (`CosmosDbService`, `BlogRetrievalService`, models, chunking, etc.). **Changes here affect both the console app and `SemanticSearch.Api`.**
- **`code/SemanticSearch.Api/`** â€” Azure Functions isolated worker (**`POST /api/search`**). Keep configuration split clear: `appsettings.Api*.json`, `host.json`, `local.settings.json` (local only; see `.gitignore`).
- **`code/SemanticSearch.Web/`** â€” Blazor WebAssembly front end. Client config belongs in **`wwwroot/appsettings*.json`** (non-secret values only). **Do not** put API keys or Cosmos credentials in anything shipped to **`wwwroot`**. **`BlazorWasmPreRendering.Build`** pre-renders on **`dotnet publish`**; keep **`Program.cs`** service registration in the **`static void ConfigureServices(...)`** local function pattern required by that package.

## Security and configuration

- **Never** commit secrets: OpenAI keys, Cosmos keys/connection strings, or tokens. Use **user secrets** locally (`dotnet user-secrets`), environment variables for CI/shells, and Azure Static Web Apps / Function **application settings** for deploy. Follow naming and precedence described in **`code/README.md`**.
- **`local.settings.json`** is for local Functions development only; keep real secrets out of committed copies (use placeholders or rely on gitignore as documented).
- Treat **`SemanticSearch.Web`** as public: anything under **`wwwroot`** can be downloaded by browsers.

## Cosmos DB, vectors, and embeddings

- **Vector dimensions** (default **768**), embedding model, and Cosmos container vector policy must stay aligned. If you change dimensions or the embedding model, you typically need a **new container** (or database) and **re-ingestion** â€” document that in the same change if you touch defaults.
- Container creation, partition key (`/id`), and `VectorDistance` query behavior live in **`CosmosDbService`**; extend there rather than duplicating Cosmos SQL in multiple places.

## Blazor, Static Web Apps, and CI

- GitHub Actions (`.github/workflows/azure-static-web-apps-*.yml`) **publishes** the Blazor client with **`dotnet publish`** so **`index.html`** and **`/_framework/*`** get correct fingerprinted asset names. **Do not** regress to uploading raw project **`wwwroot`** without publish if that would leave Blazor placeholders unfilled (see workflow comments).
- **`api_location`** points at **`code/SemanticSearch.Api`** for the Functions API. Changes to routes, `host.json`, or package versions should remain compatible with **Azure Functions v4** and **.NET 9** as used in CI.
- **`staticwebapp.config.json`** under the Web project governs routing and headers for SWA; keep it coherent with how the Blazor app calls **`/api/search`**.
- **`robots.txt`:** Lives at **`code/SemanticSearch.Web/wwwroot/robots.txt`** (deployed as **`/robots.txt`**). It must stay **directly reachable** (HTTP **200**, plain text), not rewritten to **`index.html`**. Keep **`/robots.txt`** in **`navigationFallback.exclude`** in **`staticwebapp.config.json`** whenever that fallback is edited, and do not remove or relocate the file without replacing the public **`/robots.txt`** route.

## SEO and meta (aligned with CI)

- **Document `<title>` (all routes):** Every user-facing route must set a **non-empty** document title via **`<PageTitle>`** in the owning **`.razor`** page. Shell **`index.html`** must keep a matching **`<title>`** for the home URL (first paint before Blazor runs). **Source of truth for copy and lengths:** **`code/SemanticSearch.Web/wwwroot/appsettings.json`** under **`Seo`** (see **`Seo:Home`**, **`Seo:NotFound`**, **`Seo:CanonicalBaseUrl`**, **`Seo:OgSiteName`**, **`Seo:ShareImageAlt`**, **`Seo:JsonLdSiteName`**). **`Home.razor`** and **`NotFound.razor`** must read those values through **`IConfiguration`** so runtime head tags stay aligned.
- **Home page (`/`):** **`Seo:Home:PageTitle`** must stay within **50â€“60 characters** (inclusive), and **`Seo:Home:MetaDescription`** within **110â€“160 characters** (inclusive). CI enforces this and checks that **`wwwroot/index.html`** matches **`appsettings.json`** for **`<title>`**, **`meta name="description"`**, **Open Graph** (**`og:title`**, **`og:description`**, **`og:url`**, **`og:type`**, **`og:image`**, **`og:image:alt`**, **`og:locale`**, **`og:site_name`**), **Twitter** (**`twitter:card`**, **`twitter:title`**, **`twitter:description`**, **`twitter:image`**, **`twitter:image:alt`**), **`<link rel="canonical">`**, and **JSON-LD** (**`WebSite`** with **`name`**, **`url`**, **`description`**). Run **`python scripts/check_seo_meta.py`** locally before merge when editing SEO.
- **Not-found route (`/not-found`):** **`Seo:NotFound:PageTitle`** and **`Seo:NotFound:MetaDescription`** must satisfy the **same length bands** as the home strings. The page must emit **`<meta name="robots" content="noindex, follow">`** and use **exactly one** **`<h1>`** for the visible primary heading.
- **Headings:** Keep **one** **`<h1>`** per page for the primary in-page title; use **`<h2>`**â€“**`<h6>`** for subsections (see existing **`Home.razor`** results heading).
- **HTML `lang`:** **`wwwroot/index.html`** must use **`lang="en-GB"`** on **`<html>`**.
- **Open Graph / Twitter / JSON-LD:** Follow the patterns already emitted from **`appsettings.json`**, **`index.html`**, and **`Home.razor`** **`HeadContent`**. When you add share imagery or new absolute hosts, update **`Seo:CanonicalBaseUrl`** (and any related URLs) consistently, re-run **`check_seo_meta.py`**, and keep **`staticwebapp.config.json`** coherent. Do not add inline trackers or third-party scripts without a clear need and review.
- **Language:** User-visible copy and SEO strings use **British English** spelling and punctuation where a choice exists (e.g. **en-GB** in markup and **`og:locale`**); keep technical identifiers (API names, product names) as required by vendors.

## Testing and verification

- Before merging substantive changes: **`dotnet build code/dotnet-semantic-search.sln`** (or build/publish the specific projects you touched). If you change packages, run **`dotnet restore`** first so lockfiles and restore stay consistent.
- When **`appsettings.json`**, **`index.html`**, or SEO-related Razor under **`SemanticSearch.Web`** changes, run **`python scripts/check_seo_meta.py`** from the repo root; CI runs the same script before **`dotnet publish`**.
- After dependency or TFMs changes, confirm **`SemanticSearch.Web`** still **publishes** cleanly (`dotnet publish` as in the workflow) if CI would exercise that path.

## Documentation (Markdown)

- Tracked **`*.md`** files are part of the repo contract. When behavior changes (Cosmos setup, env vars, user secrets, SWA deploy, CI steps, embedding dimensions, **SEO or `check_seo_meta.py`**, or project layout), **update every affected Markdown file in the same change** so commands and paths stay accurate.
- At minimum, keep **`code/README.md`** aligned when those areas shift; fix stale references in **`README.md`** at repo root if it still describes the solution.
- Do **not** add new Markdown files unless the user or task explicitly asks for them; prefer updating existing docs.

## Scope of changes

- Make the smallest change that satisfies the task. Do not refactor unrelated code, rename unrelated identifiers, or add NuGet packages without a clear need.
